	<div id="p169780" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner">

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p169780">Re: How to read 小火</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=169780&amp;sid=d2e36d4acb2f8e4119698751e0026a72#p169780"><img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/styles/tjp-embed/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="http://thejapanesepage.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=97876&amp;sid=d2e36d4acb2f8e4119698751e0026a72" style="color: #00AA00;" class="username-coloured">NileCat</a></strong> &raquo; Thu 04.14.2011 2:00 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">In English, you use the same word “fire” for both the intentionally made fire and the accidentally occurred fire, right?<br />In Japanese, 火 means fire in general as well. But fire accidents such as burning houses are called 火事. But only 火 doesn’t mean 火事 in most cases.<br />So, “small fire” can be translated either 小さな火 or 小さな火事. The former can be a small fire of a candle or something. And the latter means a small fire accident. (Something like “only the kitchen was burned down and the rest of the house was fine”)<br /><br />Originally:<br />ぼや＝small fire &lt;accident&gt;<br />小火=しょうか=小さな火=small fire&lt;in general&gt;<br />The origin of the word ぼやis uncertain. There seem a couple of different theories. But somewhere down the line, they started to render it using the kanji 小火. Because…it was just handy. <img src="http://thejapanesepage.com/phpbb/images/smilies/smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />(It’s much shorter than “小さな火事”, isn’t it?)<br />Then, nowadays, 小火（ぼや）is very commonly used whereas 小火（しょうか）is seldom used. （For some reason, we call them 小さな火）<br /><br />Yes, this is ateji.<br />Do you see the concept of this phrase? :<br />「本気と書いてマジと読む」（ほんきとかいてまじとよむ）<br />“Maji” is a slang based on the word “majime（真面目）” which also means serious. <br />I mean it! = 本気だよ！<br />ほんきだよ！= マジだよ！<br />Therefore: 本気（マジ）だよ！ became “popular”.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile169780">
